The Land Cruiser was initially introduced by Toyota as the Land Cruiser 2000 until 2007 when it was rebranded as the Yaris.  The model range is still quite similar today. Toyota J200 is the new model which replaced the previous J Series (J1). The J200 is available only with a 6 cylinder gasoline engine (2.3 liter V6 or 3.5 liter V8) and can be considered a sports sedan. It is built using a completely new body design (new front fascia) that is more compact than that of the previous J Series. This means that the interior is very small compared to the older J Series.
